Our application is hosted on AWS within a VPC using public and private subnets.
User traffic flows through Route 53 and an Application Load Balancer deployed in public subnets.
The ALB routes traffic to Kubernetes Ingress, which forwards requests to microservices running as pods inside an EKS cluster in private subnets.
Auto-scaling is handled using HPA based on CPU and memory metrics.
Pods access the internet through a NAT Gateway for external communication.
Jenkins handles CI/CD, builds Docker images, pushes them to ECR, and deploys to EKS.
Monitoring is done using CloudWatch and Prometheus-Grafana.â€
